message: Undid revision 1039436758 by [[Special:Contributions/Biruitorul|Biruitorul]] ([[User talk:Biruitorul|talk]]) it's on my watch list, sorry :) but it seems you also got nothing else to do, so we're both good

it seems there's something personal and/or ideological at stake here. providing external references is a lengthy process as can be evidenced from the history of the page. that however shouldn't be the reason for advancing prejudices against the page.

[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Independent journalist and activist. Interested in culture and politics. Has years of experience in international newspapers, journals and NGOs.  Focuses especially on the Middle East, South America, and the Balkans.'
misleading and malicious labels were removed.

In a nutshell the following has been done: the number of references has been more than doubled, some of the missing links have been provided, unnecessary repetitions have been deleted, useful information from some of the previous versions have been incorporated and expanded, some of the vague formulations have been made more specific, supported by corresponding references/links.
It took hours and a small team, including a native speaker of Bosnian/Croatian/Serbian, to clean up the mess done to this page God knows why and to further improve it.
[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Specialized in editing disputed or questionable texts/pages affected by conflicting worldviews or ideological positions.'

[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with '{{User sandbox}} <!-- EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->  Specialized in editing disputed or questionable texts/pages affected by conflicting worldviews or ideological positions.'

clarification here isn't necessary as more information is offered below - if the place of origin is Travnik, and that was Yugoslavia, that seems to justify the description in the first line. As far as I understand, the issue of nationality is a highly sensitive topic in this region, so it was probably wise to put this qualification as opposed to "Bosnian," "Croatian" etc.
